article.description: It figures that the Phoenix Mercury and San Antonio Silver Stars went the final 1:43 without scoring in a game during which the Mercury had to overcome a nearly eight and a-half minute drought to get its first WNBA win of the season.

article.headline: Williams sets franchise record with 16 boards
article.linkText: Mercury edge Silver Stars for first win of the season
article.story:
SAN ANTONIO (AP) -- The San Antonio Silver Stars snapped a
three-game losing streak with an 81-70 win over the Phoenix Mercury
on Saturday night.

Gwen Jackson had 15 points and 10 rebounds, and Marie Ferdinand
had 16 for the Silver Stars, who had four starters in double
figures.

Anna DeForge led the Mercury with 14 points.

The lead changed hands several times in the first half, and the
Silver Stars led 43-39 at the break after Jennifer Azzi hit a shot
from near half-court at the buzzer.

San Antonio (6-10) pushed its lead to 62-48 early in the second
half, and the Mercury (3-13) never got closer than nine after that.

San Antonio's Adrienne Goodson left with 12:20 left in the
second half with a strained right calf.
